{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/eng/frontend/19-09-14/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h3 id=\"creating-a-project\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#creating-a-project\" aria-label=\"creating a project permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Creating a Project</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Install the create-react-app module globally.</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">npm install -g create-react-app</code></pre></div>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>Create a project using the create-react-app command.</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app your-project-name</code></pre></div>\n<ol start=\"3\">\n<li>Run the app and verify it works at localhost:3000.</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">npm start</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"component-basics\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#component-basics\" aria-label=\"component basics permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Component Basics</h3>\n<p>The most fundamental concept in React is the <strong>component</strong>. React is often described as a \"component-based library,\" meaning that instead of treating a web page as a single block of HTML code, it divides the page into smaller units called components.</p>\n<p>Let's start by getting a feel for what a component looks like! The code below is what I wrote in the src/App.js file of my React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">App</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">React<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Component</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">render</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div className<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"App\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Compo <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Compo</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">React<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Component</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">render</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>p<span class=\"token operator\">></span> Compoent test<span class=\"token operator\">!</span> <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>p<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> App<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 760px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7d6c1463025228ed4503ab140bd91cdc/f79fa/19-09-14-1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 26.842105263157894%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAAFCAYAAABFA8wzAAAACXBIWXMAAAsTAAALEwEAmpwYAAAAg0lEQVR42qXMWwrCMBAF0NmO4hNEqIaWloqI4K6T9ifjNvKA7CC5NUKlXyL1wmHuzMdQISpkp5dzWeNYCIiqQXO54nZ/oKzb932zP2Cx2mK53n1FUnWQSkHlKRW6vodmBvPzQ2v+GTnnYIyB9x7WWoQQ8E8oxohRSgnTfQ7KT8ZM+9wMnSpRwvKY3EoAAAAASUVORK5CYII='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/7d6c1463025228ed4503ab140bd91cdc/15813/19-09-14-1.webp 190w,\n/static/7d6c1463025228ed4503ab140bd91cdc/1cdb2/19-09-14-1.webp 380w,\n/static/7d6c1463025228ed4503ab140bd91cdc/9046c/19-09-14-1.webp 760w,\n/static/7d6c1463025228ed4503ab140bd91cdc/e8e7c/19-09-14-1.webp 940w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/7d6c1463025228ed4503ab140bd91cdc/a2d4f/19-09-14-1.png 190w,\n/static/7d6c1463025228ed4503ab140bd91cdc/3f520/19-09-14-1.png 380w,\n/static/7d6c1463025228ed4503ab140bd91cdc/3c051/19-09-14-1.png 760w,\n/static/7d6c1463025228ed4503ab140bd91cdc/f79fa/19-09-14-1.png 940w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/7d6c1463025228ed4503ab140bd91cdc/3c051/19-09-14-1.png\"\n            alt=\"img\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>This code contains two components: App and Compo. Let's take a quick look and find the commonalities between the two components:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>They follow the <strong>class - extends React.Component</strong> pattern.</li>\n<li>They call a <strong>render</strong> method inside the class.</li>\n<li>Inside render, they call <strong>return</strong>.</li>\n<li>Inside return, there is content wrapped in a <strong>container element</strong> <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;div></code>.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"declaring-variables-in-components\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#declaring-variables-in-components\" aria-label=\"declaring variables in components permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Declaring Variables in Components</h3>\n<p>Let's look at an example that adds just a bit more to the basic component structure above. I wanted to insert a variable into the HTML content inside return, so I wrote the following code:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">App</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">React<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Component</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">render</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div className<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"App\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Compo <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Compo</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">React<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Component</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">render</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> text <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Compoent test!'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>p<span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>text<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>p<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> App<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the Compo class, you can see the line <code class=\"language-text\">let text = ...</code>. In ES6, it is recommended to use <strong>let</strong>, which has <strong>block scope</strong>, when declaring variables. So I declared the variable 'Component test!' using let. To use a variable inside the HTML code within return, simply wrap it in <strong>curly braces { }</strong> as shown above.</p>\n<h3 id=\"props-proptypes--state\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#props-proptypes--state\" aria-label=\"props proptypes  state permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>props, propTypes &#x26; state</h3>\n<p>The most common ways to handle data within a component are props and state. Props are used for handling <strong>immutable data</strong> within a component, while State is used for handling <strong>mutable, dynamic data</strong>. You can also validate prop types to reduce errors or display error logs.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>this.props.name</strong>: Used in the form <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Compo name=\"value\"/></code>.</li>\n<li><strong>this.props.children</strong>: Used in the form <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Compo> value &lt;/Compo></code>.</li>\n<li><strong>defaultProps (setting defaults)</strong>: After the component definition, use the form <code class=\"language-text\">Comp.defaultProps = { name: value }</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">App</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">React<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Component</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">render</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div className<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"App\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Compo test<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Hello world!\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> Children test <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Compo<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Compo</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">React<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Component</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">render</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>p<span class=\"token operator\">></span>propsName<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token keyword\">this</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>props<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>test<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>p<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>p<span class=\"token operator\">></span>chiledren<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token keyword\">this</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>props<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>children<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>p<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> App<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>propTypes</strong>: After the component definition, use the form <code class=\"language-text\">Comp.propTypes = { name: type }</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">Comp<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>propTypes <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\t<span class=\"token literal-property property\">value</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> React<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>PropTypes<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>string<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\t<span class=\"token literal-property property\">secondeValue</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> React<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>PropTypes<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>number\n\t<span class=\"token literal-property property\">thirdValue</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> React<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>PropTypes<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>any<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>isRequired\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>this.state</strong> (before rendering): State requires an initial value. You must set it using <code class=\"language-text\">this.state = { }</code> inside the constructor.</li>\n<li><strong>this.setState</strong> (after rendering): To modify the state value, use <code class=\"language-text\">this.setState({ ... })</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"reference\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#reference\" aria-label=\"reference permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Reference</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/little-big-programming/react%EC%9D%98-%EA%B8%B0%EB%B3%B8-%EC%BB%B4%ED%8F%AC%EB%84%8C%ED%8A%B8%EB%A5%BC-%EC%95%8C%EC%95%84%EB%B3%B4%EC%9E%90-92c923011818\">React Basics: Understanding Components</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/wasd/%EA%B8%B0%EC%B4%88%EB%B6%80%ED%84%B0-%EB%B0%B0%EC%9A%B0%EB%8A%94-react-js-1531b18f7bb2\">Learning React from Scratch, Part 1</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://velopert.com/3629\">velopert - React for Everyone #4: props and state</a></li>\n</ul>","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#creating-a-project\">Creating a Project</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#component-basics\">Component Basics</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#declaring-variables-in-components\">Declaring Variables in Components</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#props-proptypes--state\">props, propTypes &#x26; state</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#reference\">Reference</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"path":"/frontend/19-09-14/","title":"React Basics: Components","category":"FrontEnd","date":"2019-09-14"}}},"pageContext":{"postPath":"/frontend/19-09-14/","language":"eng","langRegex":"/contents/eng/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2145088972","256249292","63159454"],"slicesMap":{}}